1.title: Teen Wolf, Parks & Recreation, Melissa & Joey, NCIS: Los Angeles
1.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" takes you behind the scenes of some of your favorite television shows for exclusive set tours and interviews with the stars themselves! In this episode, we get to see where the magic happens before AND after production on ABC Family's "Melissa & Joey", we interrogate the stars of CBS's "NCIS: Los Angeles", we talk high school memories on the set of MTV's "Teen Wolf", and we play a round of interview ping-pong with the hilarious stars of NBC's "Parks and Recreation"!

3.title: Parenthood, the Middle, Franklin & Bash, How to Rock
3.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" brings you exclusive behind the scenes access to your favorite TV shows and the stars that bring them to life! This episode features life lessons and games with the stars of Nickelodeon's "How to Rock"; one-on-ones with the talented actors of NBC's "Parenthood"; an exclusive tour of the swanky set of TNT's court comedy "Franklin & Bash"; and a visit with the on-screen family from ABC's "The Middle".

4.title: The Lion King, Spider-Man, Newsies, Rocky the Musical
4.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" takes you behind the scenes of some of the hottest live musicals ever to hit a Broadway stage! We find out what it takes to move an elaborate production like 'The Lion King' from city to city; we read all about keeping it fresh performance after performance of 'Newsies'; we spar with the talented stars of 'Rocky The Musical'; and we fly high backstage at the most expensive Broadway show in history, 'Spider-Man: Turn Off The Dark'!

5.title: The Fosters, the Goldbergs, Young & Hungry, the Neighbors
5.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" ventures to the sets of some of the biggest shows on television for exclusive peeks behind the scenes and up close one-on-ones with the cast! This episode includes a 1980s flashback with the stars of ABC's "The Goldbergs", a tasty trip to the set of ABC Family's "Young & Hungry", a guided tour of the home of "The Fosters", and an out-of-this-world visit with the humans AND aliens from ABC's "The Neighbors"!

6.title: Wilfred, Community, Let's Make a Deal, Southland
6.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" brings you exclusive behind the scenes access to your favorite TV shows and the stars that bring them to life! This episode features a behind the scenes look at one of the legendary game show "Let's Make a Deal", hosted by Wayne Brady; we explore the darkly funny world of FX's "Wilfred"; we get a private lesson in how to hold a gun on the set of "Southland"; and we hang with the hilarious cast of NBC's "Community"!

8.title: Black-ish, Dog with a Blog, Kirby Buckets, Selfie
8.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" brings you exclusive behind the scenes access to your favorite TV shows and the stars that bring them to life. This episode features one-on-ones with the lovely leading ladies of ABC's "Black-ish"; getting to know the human and canine stars of Disney's "Dog with a Blog"; paling around with the young cast of "Kirby Buckets"; and finding our best angles with the talented stars of "Selfie".

9.title: Jessie, Henry Danger, the Thundermans, the Haunted Hathaways
9.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" ventures to the sets of some of the biggest shows on television for exclusive peeks behind the scenes and up close one-on-ones with the cast. This episode includes a highly educational tour of the set of Disney Channel's "Jessie"; a superhero's welcome to the set of Nickelodeon's "Henry Danger"; a superhero family affair with the cast of "The Thundermans"; and a delightfully spooky tour of the supernatural with "The Haunted Hathaways".

11.title: Fantasy Factory, Castle, Wipeout, Criminal Minds
11.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" takes you behind the scenes of some of your favorite television shows for exclusive set tours and interviews with the stars themselves! In this episode, pro-skateboarder Rob Dyrdek gives us an exclusive tour of his famous Fantasy, we go behind the scenes with the cast of ABC's "Castle", we let the double-entendres fly on the set of "Wipeout", and we pick the brains of those elite profilers from CBS's "Criminal Minds"!

12.title: Switched at Birth, Kickin' It, Perception, Vegas
12.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" takes you behind the scenes of some of your favorite television shows for exclusive set tours and interviews with the stars themselves! In this episode, the cast of Disney XD's "Kickin' It" show off their best karate moves; actor Eric McCormack gives us a private tour of the set of his TNT drama "Perception"; we practice our poker face with the cast of CBS's "Vegas"; and the stars of ABC Family's "Switched at Birth" show off their sign language skills!

-1.title: The McCarthys, Ground Floor, Scorpion, State of Affairs
-1.plot: Young Hollywood's "Quiet On The Set" takes you behind the scenes of some of your favorite television shows for exclusive set tours and interviews with the stars themselves. In this episode, Boston comes to L.A. in CBS's "The McCarthys"; just another day at the office with the cast of TBS's "Ground Floor"; testing our IQ on the set of CBS's "Scorpion"; and we go deep into the political intrigue of NBC's "State of Affairs".

imdb.plot outline: Do you love television? Are you a pop culture junkie? Get your fix with Quiet On The Set, your backstage pass to the world of Hollywood! Our YH insiders take you through their favorite set visits and share never-before-heard secrets and stories about blockbuster television and even a few Broadway musicals! This is your chance to see some of your favorite shows like you have never seen them before.
